## The Quadrant Map for Nonprofit HR

|Quadrant                 |Nonprofit Application                                      |Risk    |Nonprofit-Specific Caution                                                                                                                  |
|-------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------|--------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|**Strategic Partner**    |Succession planning for ED role, board composition strategy|HIGH    |Small orgs often have no succession depth. AI creates false confidence where honest acknowledgment of the gap is safer.                     |
|**Change Agent**         |Culture assessment, staff engagement surveys               |MODERATE|Sentiment data misused by boards without human interpretation. Small staff means individual employees may be identifiable in aggregate data.|
|**Employee Champion**    |Staff relations, accommodation, investigation response     |HIGHEST |In small orgs, the ED is often both the HR function and the subject of complaints. This conflict cannot be resolved by AI.                  |
|**Administrative Expert**|Payroll, benefits, onboarding, policy templates            |MODERATE|Most useful quadrant — but only after process accuracy is confirmed. Automating a wrong process is worse than the manual version.           |

